WEBVTT

00:02.210 --> 00:04.170
Hannah: Me and those
people at that camp,

00:04.170 --> 00:06.000
we came here to escape
a war in the future.

00:06.000 --> 00:07.420
Previously
on "The Crossing"...

00:07.420 --> 00:09.330
Caleb: Why is there
a fence going up?

00:09.330 --> 00:11.000
We have to expose this
to the public.

00:11.000 --> 00:12.580
We need evidence.
-What kind of evidence?

00:12.580 --> 00:14.170
Photos.

00:14.170 --> 00:16.250
Caleb: How can
you write in Apex?

00:16.250 --> 00:17.880
I didn't have a choice.

00:17.880 --> 00:19.920
You belonged to them.

00:19.920 --> 00:23.040
You're a cure, Reece.
You could save my life.

00:23.040 --> 00:24.750
I'm not here to save
anyone else's life.

00:24.750 --> 00:26.000
I just want Leah.

00:26.000 --> 00:27.620
Hey, baby girl.

00:27.620 --> 00:29.750
Lindauer: Agent Ren, who
apparently has gone missing...

00:29.750 --> 00:31.750
[ Gunshot ]
[ Gasping ]

00:31.750 --> 00:33.750
...she believed that there were
other future people

00:33.750 --> 00:35.170
that came earlier.

00:35.170 --> 00:37.080
This says we need to
capture the Apex alive?

00:37.080 --> 00:39.580
We have to harvest her genetic
material for this plan to work.

00:39.580 --> 00:41.000
[ Tires screech ]

00:41.000 --> 00:43.620
-[ Groans ]
-Mama!

00:43.620 --> 00:45.080
[ Groans ]

00:46.540 --> 00:51.080
♪♪

00:51.080 --> 00:56.000
♪♪

00:57.250 --> 00:59.290
We're close.

00:59.290 --> 01:03.500
♪♪

01:03.500 --> 01:07.500
♪♪

01:07.500 --> 01:11.380
♪♪

01:13.790 --> 01:15.960
[ Door clanking open ]

01:32.250 --> 01:33.710
Mama!

01:33.710 --> 01:35.670
[ Groans ]

01:35.670 --> 01:39.500
♪♪

01:39.500 --> 01:43.830
♪♪

01:43.830 --> 01:45.880
Vivek: There's no
pupillary response.

01:45.880 --> 01:47.790
We can't wake her.

01:47.790 --> 01:49.710
[ Machine beeping ]

01:53.960 --> 01:56.580
[ Monitor beeping ]

01:56.580 --> 01:59.210
♪♪

02:07.710 --> 02:12.580
♪♪

02:12.580 --> 02:15.040
-Listen.
[ Indistinct talking ]

02:15.040 --> 02:19.000
Listen, I know that there have
been some conflicting reports.

02:19.000 --> 02:21.460
No, there haven't been any
reports, that's the problem.

02:21.460 --> 02:24.080
True or false, Mayor, there are
survivors from Thorn Beach

02:24.080 --> 02:25.380
being held
up in the mountains?

02:25.380 --> 02:27.380
There have been
temporary housing set up

02:27.380 --> 02:29.250
for some people
at the old campgrounds, yes.

02:29.250 --> 02:31.290
And you didn't think
that we had a right to know?

02:31.290 --> 02:34.380
It was only recently
brought to my attention.

02:34.380 --> 02:37.620
Look, there was
some confusion early on

02:37.620 --> 02:40.290
between the local
and federal authorities.

02:40.290 --> 02:42.620
But Homeland Security
is -- is on top of this.

02:42.620 --> 02:43.880
[ Crowd murmuring ]

02:43.880 --> 02:45.670
Is that supposed to
make us feel better?

02:45.670 --> 02:47.830
[ Screeching noise ]

02:47.830 --> 02:51.210
[ Crowd grumbling ]

02:54.330 --> 02:57.250
You all know who I am.

02:57.250 --> 02:59.670
Oh, boy. I don't.
Do you?

02:59.670 --> 03:03.290
There's a conspiracy going on
right under our noses,

03:03.290 --> 03:05.830
and here's the proof.

03:05.830 --> 03:07.210
[ Crowd murmuring ]

03:07.210 --> 03:08.460
Where'd he get that?

03:08.460 --> 03:10.380
You may ask
where I got this.

03:10.380 --> 03:12.290
I've been in contact
with them.

03:12.290 --> 03:16.420
They are American, and they are
being held against their will!

03:16.420 --> 03:19.120
Truth is, we don't know
where they're from.

03:19.120 --> 03:20.500
Yeah, but we know
where they are.

03:20.500 --> 03:22.170
So why don't we all go there
and see for ourselves?

03:22.170 --> 03:23.670
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

03:23.670 --> 03:25.040
You've got American citizens
up there

03:25.040 --> 03:25.920
being held
against their will?

03:25.920 --> 03:27.330
It's complicated.

03:27.330 --> 03:31.750
Today it is them,
tomorrow it could be you!

03:31.750 --> 03:33.750
[ Crowd shouting ]

03:33.750 --> 03:36.250
Now, are we just gonna sit here
and let this happen?

03:36.250 --> 03:37.620
-Man: No!
-[ Crowd murmuring ]

03:37.620 --> 03:38.880
What are we gonna do?

03:38.880 --> 03:41.000
[ Indistinct shouting ]

03:45.210 --> 03:47.380
-Uhh--
-Uhh, this isn't good.

03:47.380 --> 03:49.460
-No.
-All right, come on.

03:52.330 --> 03:55.880
♪♪

03:55.880 --> 03:59.460
♪♪

04:02.710 --> 04:03.540
Good morning.

04:03.540 --> 04:05.420
Hey, Paul.

04:07.540 --> 04:11.460
Hey, any word on when
Emma might be coming back?

04:11.460 --> 04:13.620
I guess
she's still out sick.

04:13.620 --> 04:15.290
I hope
it's nothing serious.

04:15.290 --> 04:16.960
I'm sure
she'll be back soon.

04:16.960 --> 04:18.500
[ Exhales sharply ]

04:18.500 --> 04:20.460
Anything
I could do for you?

04:20.460 --> 04:21.880
Nah.

04:21.880 --> 04:23.000
[ Chuckles softly ]

04:25.380 --> 04:27.380
Wonder if they made it.

04:27.380 --> 04:29.750
'89 was a long time ago.

04:29.750 --> 04:31.040
[ Inhales deeply ]

04:31.040 --> 04:32.420
It depends on
how you look at it.

04:32.420 --> 04:34.330
Yeah.

04:34.330 --> 04:36.920
You have a wife?
Husband?

04:36.920 --> 04:38.080
Me?

04:38.080 --> 04:39.330
Nah.

04:39.330 --> 04:40.620
Haven't found
the right one.

04:40.620 --> 04:42.040
Hmm.

04:42.040 --> 04:43.250
I'll know it when I see it,
I guess.

04:43.250 --> 04:44.880
You will.

04:44.880 --> 04:46.750
And when you do,
don't hesitate.

04:46.750 --> 04:49.750
You'll want that time
to look back on.

04:55.210 --> 05:01.210
♪♪

05:01.380 --> 05:02.880
Hey.

05:02.880 --> 05:07.790
♪♪

05:07.790 --> 05:13.040
♪♪

05:13.040 --> 05:15.960
You know, maybe Leah's
where she...

05:15.960 --> 05:17.710
where she needs to be.

05:17.710 --> 05:19.880
With an Apex.

05:19.880 --> 05:22.250
Whatever she is,
Leah loves her.

05:22.250 --> 05:25.170
And I have to believe
she's gonna be okay.

05:26.580 --> 05:28.580
How do you do it?

05:28.580 --> 05:32.080
Just...let go,

05:32.080 --> 05:33.960
like it means nothing?

05:33.960 --> 05:35.790
Well, it's not nothing.

05:35.790 --> 05:38.250
We left our daughter.

05:38.250 --> 05:41.420
We didn't leave her.
She was taken from us.

05:41.420 --> 05:44.120
We left behind any chance
of ever seeing her again.

05:44.120 --> 05:46.540
And you think
that was easy for me?

05:47.830 --> 05:49.750
I don't blame you.

05:50.830 --> 05:55.540
In a way, I envy you.

05:55.540 --> 05:58.420
Because
I can't let go of it.

06:00.000 --> 06:03.120
Rebecca, we didn't
have a choice.

06:05.750 --> 06:07.170
[ Footsteps approaching ]

06:07.170 --> 06:11.250
♪♪

06:11.250 --> 06:15.330
♪♪

06:15.330 --> 06:16.750
[ Knock on door ]

06:18.460 --> 06:19.460
Hi.

06:19.460 --> 06:20.460
Hello.

06:20.460 --> 06:22.380
I'm Rebecca.

06:22.380 --> 06:24.080
Come in.

06:24.080 --> 06:28.580
♪♪

06:28.580 --> 06:32.830
♪♪

06:32.830 --> 06:37.380
♪♪

06:37.380 --> 06:39.040
[ Door closes ]

06:43.580 --> 06:46.250
We had a daughter,

06:46.250 --> 06:49.790
and she was taken by Apex,
just like you.

06:49.790 --> 06:52.790
I never knew what
happened to her,

06:52.790 --> 06:55.330
or why they wanted her.

06:55.330 --> 06:59.170
So I was -- I was hoping
you could help me understand.

06:59.170 --> 07:02.880
She was special.
She was smart.

07:02.880 --> 07:06.500
Perhaps a bit different.
Like me.

07:06.500 --> 07:08.620
Yeah. Yes.

07:08.620 --> 07:10.330
Rachel.

07:10.330 --> 07:12.830
Rachel was her name.

07:12.830 --> 07:15.500
She was taken because
she was neuro-diverse,

07:15.500 --> 07:20.330
a status dismissed in this era
with terms like "autism."

07:20.330 --> 07:23.210
A condition Apex engineered
out of their own germ line

07:23.210 --> 07:25.000
in a quest
for the perfect genome.

07:25.000 --> 07:27.670
But they came to realize

07:27.670 --> 07:31.000
that these afflictions sometimes
offered savant abilities

07:31.000 --> 07:33.210
not even they could match --

07:33.210 --> 07:38.620
math, language,
pattern recognition.

07:38.620 --> 07:41.960
Apex found
these abilities useful.

07:41.960 --> 07:44.460
So she was made to work?

07:44.460 --> 07:47.250
I never met
your daughter,

07:47.250 --> 07:49.960
so I couldn't tell you
what her task was,

07:49.960 --> 07:54.080
but Apex knew we functioned
better in groups.

07:54.080 --> 07:58.460
So I can tell you
that Rachel was never alone.

07:58.460 --> 08:02.790
♪♪

08:02.790 --> 08:05.210
[ Sniffles ]
And what was your task?

08:05.210 --> 08:07.500
♪♪

08:07.500 --> 08:09.120
History.

08:11.750 --> 08:13.170
Vivek:
Open your eyes.

08:15.040 --> 08:17.170
I know you're in there.

08:19.830 --> 08:22.000
We haven't been able
to elicit a response.

08:22.000 --> 08:24.420
I can't wake her.

08:24.420 --> 08:27.040
"Wake her"?
They barely sleep, right?

08:27.040 --> 08:30.000
It's not sleep.
It's something else.

08:30.000 --> 08:31.830
A dormant state.

08:31.830 --> 08:33.880
A defense mechanism.

08:33.880 --> 08:36.170
What difference does it
make if she's awake?

08:36.170 --> 08:38.460
We don't need
to access her dreams.

08:38.460 --> 08:40.880
We need her genetic code.
So slice her open and get it.

08:40.880 --> 08:42.920
It's not that simple.

08:42.920 --> 08:45.120
All metabolic processes
in her body have halted.

08:45.120 --> 08:47.620
Any cells we extract
from her die in seconds.

08:47.620 --> 08:50.120
We can't recover
intact DNA.

08:50.120 --> 08:53.120
We can't create what we want
if we can't study the code.

08:53.120 --> 08:54.670
Can she hear us?

08:54.670 --> 08:56.460
♪♪

08:56.460 --> 08:57.830
It's possible.

08:57.830 --> 08:59.290
Her readings suggest

08:59.290 --> 09:01.420
some responsiveness
to the environment.

09:01.420 --> 09:03.040
Well, we do
have the girl.

09:03.040 --> 09:05.620
We bring her here,
maybe she'll wake her up.

09:05.620 --> 09:07.080
You want to bring
a Mantle's carrier

09:07.080 --> 09:08.620
into a sterile
lab environment?

09:08.620 --> 09:09.880
She's been treated.

09:09.880 --> 09:11.920
For now. For all we know
the stress of seeing

09:11.920 --> 09:14.040
her mother like this
could trigger another flare-up.

09:14.040 --> 09:16.000
You have a better idea?

09:16.000 --> 09:18.500
[ Monitor beeping ]

09:18.500 --> 09:20.080
I might.

09:22.040 --> 09:24.620
[ Exhales sharply ]

09:24.620 --> 09:26.830
Dr. Forbin?

09:26.830 --> 09:28.750
Mr. Lindauer.

09:28.750 --> 09:31.880
I got your messages. I'm sorry.
I've been a bit, uh, busy.

09:31.880 --> 09:34.790
Yeah, well...me too.

09:37.880 --> 09:39.830
[ P.A. system hums ]

09:39.830 --> 09:43.000
[ Indistinct announcement ]

09:48.210 --> 09:51.460
I hear your prognosis
is not good.

09:51.460 --> 09:53.710
That's an understatement.

09:53.710 --> 09:56.080
If only there were some way
to surmount the limitations

09:56.080 --> 09:57.880
of modern medicine...

09:57.880 --> 09:59.920
you could be saved.

09:59.920 --> 10:03.040
I know about the research
you've been doing.

10:03.040 --> 10:05.210
And who you've been
doing it with.

10:06.790 --> 10:08.790
Sophie:
Reece, you're a cure.

10:08.790 --> 10:11.000
You're the answer to every
human illness, every defect.

10:11.000 --> 10:14.250
I mean, do you have any idea
how many lives you could save?

10:14.250 --> 10:17.290
Not 50 years from now,
not 200 -- today.

10:17.290 --> 10:19.460
Reece: I'm not here to save
anyone else's life.

10:19.460 --> 10:20.880
I just want Leah.

10:20.880 --> 10:22.750
You could save my life!

10:22.750 --> 10:25.620
You recorded my calls?

10:25.620 --> 10:28.960
You aided and abetted a killer.
Let's call it a push.

10:28.960 --> 10:31.330
You had to wonder
who you were dealing with

10:31.330 --> 10:34.170
after what she did to the
rent-a-cop in that college lab.

10:34.170 --> 10:35.170
[ Gasps ]

10:35.170 --> 10:37.580
And trust me,
that was nothing.

10:37.580 --> 10:40.170
She's killed good men.
My men.

10:40.170 --> 10:42.210
You're lucky to be alive.

10:42.210 --> 10:45.080
Why are you here?

10:45.080 --> 10:48.040
To tell
you it's not too late.

10:48.040 --> 10:49.750
Your research can continue.

10:49.750 --> 10:51.750
You can be saved.

10:51.750 --> 10:55.040
♪♪

10:55.040 --> 10:57.710
But I need something
from you first.

10:57.710 --> 11:00.500
♪♪

11:04.380 --> 11:06.290
♪♪

11:06.290 --> 11:07.920
We got to get ahead
of this.

11:07.920 --> 11:10.170
If these people get up there,
storm the camp?

11:10.170 --> 11:11.380
-It could get ugly.
-Yeah.

11:11.380 --> 11:13.330
Call the station, get
everybody to the mountain.

11:13.330 --> 11:16.290
Roadblock at the base,
no one gets past, okay?

11:16.290 --> 11:18.120
Roger that.
What about you?

11:18.120 --> 11:20.960
I'm gonna talk to the federal
agent that came to the office.

11:20.960 --> 11:22.500
What's his name?
-Foster.

11:22.500 --> 11:24.330
Right. I'm gonna go
talk to him at the camp

11:24.330 --> 11:25.540
and give him a heads up.

11:25.540 --> 11:27.880
Maybe he can make sure
his people don't overreact.

11:27.880 --> 11:30.380
Copy that.
Excuse me.

11:30.380 --> 11:34.210
[ Siren wailing ]

11:34.210 --> 11:35.540
Marshall: What's up?

11:35.540 --> 11:37.380
Dude, we're heading
up to the camp.

11:37.380 --> 11:39.710
Get off your ass
and join the revolution.

11:39.710 --> 11:41.620
Go for it. I'm good.

11:41.620 --> 11:43.620
It's your girlfriend
we're trying to help.

11:43.620 --> 11:45.120
She's not my girlfriend.

11:45.120 --> 11:46.380
She's not gonna be,
either.

11:46.380 --> 11:47.380
What?

11:47.380 --> 11:48.620
I mean, like...

11:48.620 --> 11:50.080
there's something
wrong with her.

11:50.080 --> 11:52.210
Maybe those people are up there
for a reason, you know?

11:52.210 --> 11:53.500
Whatever, man.

11:53.500 --> 11:55.290
If you change your mind,
you know where to find me.

11:55.290 --> 11:56.790
-Okay, listen, I g--
-[ Click ]

11:58.880 --> 12:04.000
♪♪

12:04.000 --> 12:09.040
♪♪

12:09.040 --> 12:10.460
What's that?

12:11.710 --> 12:13.460
Um...

12:13.460 --> 12:16.750
When I was four,
I stole my sister's bike.

12:16.750 --> 12:18.830
I was a natural,

12:18.830 --> 12:21.500
rode it right through the lanes
of our apple orchard...

12:21.500 --> 12:23.120
until I hit a tree.

12:23.120 --> 12:24.750
Broke my arm
in two places.

12:24.750 --> 12:27.210
When I got the cast off,

12:27.210 --> 12:29.960
my mom used the apples
from that tree to make a pie.

12:34.210 --> 12:37.000
Best pie I ever had.

12:40.790 --> 12:42.080
[ Clears throat ]

12:42.080 --> 12:44.420
Does this mean
you're not made at me anymore?

12:44.420 --> 12:46.080
I'm not mad at you.

12:48.290 --> 12:50.120
Truth is
I barely know you.

12:53.880 --> 12:56.080
But I want to.

13:01.000 --> 13:03.000
Starting with this.

13:03.000 --> 13:07.710
♪♪

13:07.710 --> 13:09.330
You went back for it?

13:09.330 --> 13:11.880
Yeah.
And I opened it.

13:11.880 --> 13:15.000
♪♪

13:15.000 --> 13:16.920
Why do you have
a picture of him?

13:16.920 --> 13:20.330
♪♪

13:20.330 --> 13:21.960
What have you heard
about us?

13:21.960 --> 13:24.000
About where we're from?

13:26.290 --> 13:28.420
Nothing that makes sense.

13:28.420 --> 13:31.040
That you're in
protective custody,

13:31.040 --> 13:33.000
you're from
some cult, or...

13:33.000 --> 13:34.500
Or that we're from
another time?

13:34.500 --> 13:36.250
[ Laughs ] Yeah.
Yeah, I heard that.

13:38.620 --> 13:40.170
[ Laughs ]

13:40.170 --> 13:42.710
Come on, Hannah.

13:42.710 --> 13:45.120
That's not possible.

13:45.120 --> 13:48.210
A lot of things
will become possible.

13:48.210 --> 13:52.120
♪♪

13:52.120 --> 13:57.040
Where -- Where I'm from,
there are no orchards.

13:57.040 --> 14:00.420
I broke my arm, too.

14:01.960 --> 14:05.420
Running from people
who were hunting me.

14:05.420 --> 14:09.670
My dad and I were the only ones
left alive in my family,

14:09.670 --> 14:13.460
and I left him to come here.

14:13.460 --> 14:15.960
Everyone in this camp
has a story like mine.

14:15.960 --> 14:19.790
♪♪

14:19.790 --> 14:24.250
♪♪

14:24.250 --> 14:26.620
The person who gave me
this locket

14:26.620 --> 14:29.330
told me the picture inside
was of someone important,

14:29.330 --> 14:30.710
someone who would
protect me.

14:30.710 --> 14:32.880
Is it true?
I don't know.

14:32.880 --> 14:35.250
But if this made its way
to me then,

14:35.250 --> 14:38.170
and all the way back to me
here today...

14:38.170 --> 14:40.790
I can't just ignore that.

14:40.790 --> 14:44.080
♪♪

14:44.080 --> 14:46.420
Hey.
Is everything okay?

14:46.420 --> 14:49.120
I found something.

14:49.120 --> 14:51.330
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

14:51.330 --> 14:55.380
♪♪

14:55.380 --> 14:59.460
♪♪

14:59.460 --> 15:03.620
♪♪

15:03.620 --> 15:07.620
♪♪

15:07.620 --> 15:09.000
What is it?

15:09.000 --> 15:13.670
♪♪

15:13.670 --> 15:18.580
♪♪

15:18.580 --> 15:23.040
♪♪

15:30.920 --> 15:32.880
[ Brakes squeal ]

15:32.880 --> 15:36.880
♪♪

15:36.880 --> 15:38.580
Well, look who's back.

15:38.580 --> 15:40.290
I have a situation.

15:40.290 --> 15:43.540
There's a mob in town, and
they're headed right here.

15:43.540 --> 15:45.880
I need to talk
to Agent Foster.

15:45.880 --> 15:48.210
All right, hold here.

15:48.210 --> 15:51.120
[ Police radio chatter ]

15:57.920 --> 16:00.670
All of this is history?

16:00.670 --> 16:02.790
Naomi: Yes.

16:02.790 --> 16:06.040
They let you learn?

16:06.040 --> 16:08.620
In the entirety
of human civilization,

16:08.620 --> 16:11.880
100% of empires
eventually fell.

16:11.880 --> 16:16.540
Apex was essentially
an empire.

16:16.540 --> 16:19.920
They used people like me
to analyze the patterns,

16:19.920 --> 16:24.250
find a way for them
to sustain their structure.

16:24.250 --> 16:28.540
But I got away,
then I came here...

16:28.540 --> 16:30.920
and, in the water...

16:33.540 --> 16:35.250
...I died.

16:37.040 --> 16:39.040
But then I rose.

16:41.500 --> 16:47.500
In our time, I was a slave,
but here I am a prophet.

16:47.580 --> 16:52.580
♪♪

16:52.580 --> 16:54.540
Can I trust you?

16:57.920 --> 17:00.540
The things I need to do
I can't do in here.

17:00.540 --> 17:02.880
I'm going to leave.

17:02.880 --> 17:05.830
And I need people
with me...

17:05.830 --> 17:07.670
people like you.

17:07.670 --> 17:13.170
♪♪

17:13.170 --> 17:14.830
[ Vehicle approaches ]

17:20.540 --> 17:21.710
Hey.

17:21.710 --> 17:23.880
I'm glad you're here.
You saved me a call.

17:23.880 --> 17:26.750
I need to show you
something.

17:26.750 --> 17:29.250
Wait, you want me
to come in?

17:29.250 --> 17:31.500
Yeah.

17:31.500 --> 17:33.080
[ Crowd shouting indistinctly ]

17:33.080 --> 17:36.380
No one is heading out here!
Please disperse!

17:36.380 --> 17:39.330
Please disperse now!

17:39.330 --> 17:40.960
Hold this.

17:40.960 --> 17:43.170
[ Shouting continues ]

17:46.420 --> 17:48.120
-Hey.
-Hey.

17:48.120 --> 17:49.670
Yeah, how's it going
down there?

17:49.670 --> 17:52.040
Uh, it's under control.
For now.

17:52.040 --> 17:53.830
Okay, good.

17:53.830 --> 17:56.330
I'm at the gate with Foster.
I'm going up to the camp.

17:56.330 --> 17:57.960
So keep me apprised.

17:57.960 --> 17:59.380
Roger that.

17:59.380 --> 18:00.670
[ Shouting continues ]

18:02.380 --> 18:04.170
All right, let's go.

18:04.170 --> 18:09.250
♪♪

18:09.250 --> 18:11.210
[ Engine starts ]

18:15.040 --> 18:16.420
[ Crowd shouting ]

18:16.420 --> 18:18.210
Hey, hey, hey, hey!
Get this guy in cuffs!

18:18.210 --> 18:19.460
Cuff this guy!
Cuff him!

18:19.460 --> 18:22.250
Stand back! Stay back!
People, back!

18:22.250 --> 18:24.540
Ma'am, hands behind your back.
-No!

18:24.540 --> 18:26.580
-Hands behind your --
-What are you doing?!

18:26.580 --> 18:27.920
You are under arrest.

18:27.920 --> 18:29.750
[ Shouting continues ]

18:29.750 --> 18:33.960
Last time I was here, I barreled
headfirst through your gate.

18:33.960 --> 18:36.380
Jacked up my push bar.

18:36.380 --> 18:38.380
Now I'm getting
a personal tour.

18:38.380 --> 18:40.210
Order came from the top.

18:41.750 --> 18:43.080
Lindauer?

18:45.960 --> 18:47.790
Hey, where is everybody?

18:47.790 --> 18:49.880
Camp's on lockdown
on the other side.

18:49.880 --> 18:51.620
Lockdown?

18:53.420 --> 18:55.420
[ Exhales sharply ]

18:55.420 --> 19:00.880
♪♪

19:00.880 --> 19:02.210
We found her car

19:02.210 --> 19:04.580
yesterday
near the back entrance.

19:04.580 --> 19:08.290
♪♪

19:08.290 --> 19:09.960
Emma.

19:09.960 --> 19:12.040
[ Exhales ]

19:12.040 --> 19:15.960
♪♪

19:20.710 --> 19:22.380
[ Breathing heavily ]

19:22.380 --> 19:23.790
I'm fine.

19:29.880 --> 19:32.380
[ Monitor beeping ]

19:34.460 --> 19:36.380
Lindauer: I did say
it would be difficult.

19:36.380 --> 19:41.250
[ Exhales sharply ]
This seems...extreme.

19:41.250 --> 19:43.330
No, we need to take
precautions.

19:43.330 --> 19:45.540
As I said,
she's dangerous.

19:45.540 --> 19:48.620
But if we can study the curative
properties of her genetic code,

19:48.620 --> 19:51.330
it's like you said...
we can save millions of lives.

19:51.330 --> 19:52.620
[ Exhales sharply ]

19:52.620 --> 19:55.250
Yeah, but I didn't need
a cage to do my work.

19:55.250 --> 19:57.210
She cooperated
willingly.

19:57.210 --> 19:59.960
And our hope is that,
with your help, she will again.

19:59.960 --> 20:01.620
[ Exhales ]
What do you mean?

20:01.620 --> 20:04.120
Vivek:
She's entered a dormant state.

20:04.120 --> 20:06.750
We need to get her out of it
and keep her engaged

20:06.750 --> 20:09.670
long enough to extract viable
cells and other materials.

20:09.670 --> 20:12.460
[ Exhales ]

20:12.460 --> 20:15.380
If I "engage" her, you'll...

20:15.380 --> 20:17.620
let me continue
with my research?

20:17.620 --> 20:19.830
Yes.

20:19.830 --> 20:21.880
[ Exhales ]

20:21.880 --> 20:24.500
♪♪

20:27.040 --> 20:30.080
[ Heartbeat thumping ]

20:30.080 --> 20:32.540
Mama!

20:36.290 --> 20:37.420
Sophie: Reece...

20:37.420 --> 20:41.460
[ Heartbeat quickening ]

20:41.460 --> 20:43.710
Reece, it's Sophie...

20:43.710 --> 20:46.120
[ Heartbeat quickening ]

20:46.120 --> 20:48.580
Reece, wake up.

20:48.580 --> 20:50.790
[ Gasps ]

20:53.460 --> 20:55.000
Are you okay?

20:56.460 --> 20:58.750
Where is Leah?

20:58.750 --> 21:04.670
♪♪

21:04.670 --> 21:07.750
What if the doctor
figures out what we're doing?

21:07.750 --> 21:11.120
She's dying.
She won't last the week.

21:11.120 --> 21:12.710
And if she does?

21:12.710 --> 21:14.210
She won't.

21:19.170 --> 21:22.380
Bryce: I just don't know why
anyone here would do this.

21:22.380 --> 21:24.420
Maybe it wasn't
somebody up here.

21:24.420 --> 21:28.040
She's been missing
for 10 days.

21:28.040 --> 21:30.080
Don't you find it
a little strange

21:30.080 --> 21:31.750
it took so long
to find her?

21:31.750 --> 21:33.290
It's a big camp.

21:33.290 --> 21:35.120
I guess so...

21:35.120 --> 21:37.330
seeing that no one
heard the gunshot.

21:40.170 --> 21:42.750
Her gun is missing.

21:42.750 --> 21:44.920
9mm Sig Sauer.

21:44.920 --> 21:46.920
If we find it on
the grounds, we'll know.

21:46.920 --> 21:48.040
Excuse me.
Agent Foster?

21:55.040 --> 21:56.670
Just received
confirmation.

21:56.670 --> 21:58.830
We're all accounted for
in the mess hall.

21:58.830 --> 22:00.040
Start a cabin search.

22:00.040 --> 22:02.250
If you find anything,
report back directly to me.

22:02.250 --> 22:04.170
Understood.

22:04.170 --> 22:08.580
♪♪

22:08.580 --> 22:13.290
♪♪

22:13.290 --> 22:17.500
♪♪

22:17.500 --> 22:18.880
Man: Give me a hand!

22:18.880 --> 22:22.380
♪♪

22:22.380 --> 22:25.880
♪♪

22:25.880 --> 22:28.380
[ Indistinct hushed
conversations ]

22:30.540 --> 22:34.750
♪♪

22:34.750 --> 22:39.250
♪♪

22:39.250 --> 22:44.460
♪♪

22:44.460 --> 22:47.120
They found a body.
That's what this is about.

22:47.120 --> 22:48.290
A body? What body?

22:48.290 --> 22:49.710
I don't know.

22:49.710 --> 22:54.750
♪♪

22:54.750 --> 23:00.000
♪♪

23:00.000 --> 23:05.380
♪♪

23:05.380 --> 23:10.420
♪♪

23:10.420 --> 23:12.040
Hey.

23:12.040 --> 23:15.040
♪♪

23:15.040 --> 23:18.250
9mm Sig Sauer.

23:18.250 --> 23:19.290
Let's go.

23:30.290 --> 23:31.620
You need to come with us.

23:32.960 --> 23:34.210
Me?

23:35.750 --> 23:37.210
Why?
-Come on, let's go.

23:37.210 --> 23:39.500
Hey...hey, the man
can stand on his own.

23:39.500 --> 23:41.540
Back off.

23:41.540 --> 23:42.960
Caleb.

23:42.960 --> 23:44.880
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

23:44.880 --> 23:47.670
♪♪

23:47.670 --> 23:49.460
[ Handcuffs locking ]
-[ Groans ]

23:49.460 --> 23:50.920
You're making
a big mistake here.

23:50.920 --> 23:52.170
Agent: Move it.

23:52.170 --> 23:53.500
Ow. You're making
a terrible mistake.

23:53.500 --> 23:55.420
-I don't get it.
-What's that?

23:55.420 --> 23:57.290
He was looking for her
this morning.

23:57.290 --> 23:58.460
-Nice and easy.
-Agent Ren.

23:58.460 --> 23:59.960
You're making
a mistake, all right?

23:59.960 --> 24:01.880
-Paul, you got to calm down.
-I have nothing --

24:01.880 --> 24:03.120
I have nothing to do
with this.

24:03.120 --> 24:04.330
Get him out of here.
Calm down.

24:04.330 --> 24:06.670
Ahh! Just stop and listen,
okay?!

24:06.670 --> 24:08.580
I had nothing to do with this!
You got to believe me!

24:08.580 --> 24:09.960
[ Door opens ]
You got to believe me!

24:13.580 --> 24:15.960
♪♪

24:15.960 --> 24:19.170
[ Indistinct shouting ]

24:19.170 --> 24:20.830
Listen up!

24:20.830 --> 24:22.580
[ Shouting continues ]

24:25.620 --> 24:27.170
[ Clears throat ]

24:27.170 --> 24:29.330
I have a report from the camp.

24:29.330 --> 24:30.880
[ Crowd quiets ]

24:30.880 --> 24:32.880
They found human remains

24:32.880 --> 24:36.210
they believe to be the body
of a federal agent.

24:36.210 --> 24:37.710
Woman: What?!
[ Crowd murmuring ]

24:37.710 --> 24:39.710
The agents up there,
along with the Sheriff,

24:39.710 --> 24:41.380
need to conduct
an investigation.

24:41.380 --> 24:43.580
There are gonna be vehicles
coming up and down this road.

24:43.580 --> 24:48.790
So I really need you
to disperse...now.

24:48.790 --> 24:52.790
Or if you still want to go
to jail for those people,

24:52.790 --> 24:55.120
that can be arranged.

24:55.120 --> 24:58.880
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:01.960 --> 25:04.330
[ Exhales deeply ]

25:04.330 --> 25:08.920
♪♪

25:08.920 --> 25:13.790
♪♪

25:13.790 --> 25:16.330
Hey. I'm Jude Ellis.
I'm the sheriff.

25:16.330 --> 25:18.170
I believe you.

25:18.170 --> 25:20.500
I-I don't know
what's happening.

25:20.500 --> 25:21.710
Can you help me?

25:21.710 --> 25:23.830
I don't know,
but I'm gonna try.

25:23.830 --> 25:27.080
Look, if they give you a call
or if you can get to a phone,

25:27.080 --> 25:29.540
you call me, okay?

25:29.540 --> 25:31.670
Yes, sir,
we have a suspect.

25:31.670 --> 25:33.290
It's Paul.

25:33.290 --> 25:34.540
We found the gun
in his cabin.

25:34.540 --> 25:36.330
Good work.

25:36.330 --> 25:37.960
Thank the Sheriff
for his assistance

25:37.960 --> 25:39.120
and escort him
off the site.

25:41.880 --> 25:44.830
Is that a problem?

25:44.830 --> 25:47.500
The Sheriff said there was
almost a riot in town today.

25:47.500 --> 25:48.830
If we want to be transparent,

25:48.830 --> 25:50.790
it might be a good idea
to keep him involved.

25:50.790 --> 25:52.540
It's a federal matter now.

25:52.540 --> 25:54.040
Get him off the site.

25:54.040 --> 25:55.710
Yes, sir.

25:55.710 --> 25:56.540
[ Cellphone clicks ]

26:03.000 --> 26:06.040
-Sheriff.
-Yeah?

26:06.040 --> 26:08.120
I'm supposed to show you
off the property.

26:08.120 --> 26:10.330
Let me guess --
orders from the top.

26:12.830 --> 26:14.330
[ Exhales ]

26:17.330 --> 26:20.580
Don't believe them.

26:20.580 --> 26:22.790
Whatever they're telling you
that they'd doing here,

26:22.790 --> 26:24.170
it's a lie.

26:24.170 --> 26:26.790
[ Monitor beeping ]

26:26.790 --> 26:29.250
We've all seen
what your body can do.

26:29.250 --> 26:32.290
They say they're...

26:32.290 --> 26:34.790
"mining
its curative properties."

26:34.790 --> 26:38.620
No, that's what you're
doing...isn't it?

26:38.620 --> 26:40.540
Repairing your heart.

26:41.880 --> 26:43.710
I can hear it.

26:43.710 --> 26:46.040
You're dying.

26:46.040 --> 26:48.000
My heart's just a symptom.

26:48.000 --> 26:51.080
If I fix it today, tomorrow
it's cancer.

26:51.080 --> 26:54.580
Or Alzheimer's.
Or any other number of diseases.

26:54.580 --> 26:58.120
We're vulnerable to so much
that you aren't.

27:00.460 --> 27:03.460
What exactly is it that you
think you can accomplish?

27:03.460 --> 27:06.120
Analysis of your DNA
should make it possible

27:06.120 --> 27:08.830
to initiate
a cellular upgrade.

27:08.830 --> 27:11.290
You can't make yourself
like me.

27:11.290 --> 27:15.790
No...but I should be able to
transfer specific features.

27:15.790 --> 27:17.880
You don't understand.

27:17.880 --> 27:20.580
Only 7%
of your population

27:20.580 --> 27:24.210
has a genetic marker
that will make Apex possible.

27:24.210 --> 27:27.880
If you don't have it
and you try this,

27:27.880 --> 27:30.040
you will die.

27:30.040 --> 27:33.120
Don't do it.

27:33.120 --> 27:37.000
♪♪

27:37.000 --> 27:40.080
[ Gloves snapping ]

27:43.250 --> 27:45.620
I'm not gonna
leave you here.

27:45.620 --> 27:48.670
I'll come back for you.
I promise.

27:48.670 --> 27:53.460
♪♪

27:53.460 --> 27:56.500
[ Sighs ]

28:01.460 --> 28:03.380
[ Door unlocks ]

28:09.830 --> 28:11.040
[ Door closes ]

28:12.830 --> 28:15.210
Hello, Paul.

28:15.210 --> 28:17.290
♪♪

28:17.290 --> 28:18.960
Eve...

28:18.960 --> 28:22.380
♪♪

28:22.380 --> 28:25.040
[ Breathing heavily ]

28:25.040 --> 28:27.540
♪♪

28:27.540 --> 28:29.880
Pl--

28:29.880 --> 28:33.380
P-- But I don't understand.

28:33.380 --> 28:35.920
It's okay.
I'll explain it all to you.

28:35.920 --> 28:38.710
-[ Sobbing ]
-Everything's gonna be okay now.

28:38.710 --> 28:42.000
♪♪

28:42.000 --> 28:45.880
♪♪

28:45.880 --> 28:48.120
[ Exhales ]

28:53.750 --> 28:56.750
[ Sighs ]
I can't believe it.

28:59.420 --> 29:00.880
You look...

29:00.880 --> 29:02.620
Older.

29:02.620 --> 29:04.920
It's been a long time.

29:04.920 --> 29:06.750
I saw you two months ago.

29:06.750 --> 29:09.330
Paul, no.

29:09.330 --> 29:11.580
♪♪

29:11.580 --> 29:13.380
I've been here
for 10 years.

29:13.380 --> 29:16.460
We came back
to different times.

29:16.460 --> 29:20.620
When you crossed,
something must've gone wrong.

29:20.620 --> 29:23.210
Yeah. But...

29:25.290 --> 29:27.290
It was a rush when we left.

29:27.290 --> 29:30.790
It was -- It was...chaos.

29:30.790 --> 29:33.620
I'm surprised any of us
made it at all.

29:33.620 --> 29:37.380
♪♪

29:37.380 --> 29:41.710
♪♪

29:41.710 --> 29:43.460
[ Voice breaking ]
10 years.

29:43.460 --> 29:45.920
Yeah.

29:47.540 --> 29:49.500
[ Laughs ]

29:49.500 --> 29:51.420
You'd never know.

29:52.960 --> 29:54.880
[ Laughs ]

29:54.880 --> 29:58.120
You look more beautiful
than I've ever seen you.

29:58.120 --> 29:59.710
[ Exhales ]

29:59.710 --> 30:01.710
They have cosmetics here.

30:01.710 --> 30:02.920
They work wonders.

30:02.920 --> 30:05.210
[ Laughs ]

30:08.000 --> 30:11.040
I'm so sorry, Paul.

30:13.040 --> 30:15.620
I'm sorry I didn't tell you
I was leaving.

30:17.670 --> 30:20.500
I knew if I looked you in
the eyes that I couldn't go.

30:20.500 --> 30:22.670
And that'd I'd feel
just how I feel now,

30:22.670 --> 30:25.210
and I'd never want to be
apart from you again.

30:25.210 --> 30:27.040
But I had to go.

30:28.920 --> 30:30.750
For the cause.

30:30.750 --> 30:33.420
Stopping Apex.

30:33.420 --> 30:36.210
But it didn't work.

30:36.210 --> 30:39.330
And we realized that the moment
you and the others showed up.

30:39.330 --> 30:42.960
♪♪

30:42.960 --> 30:47.210
♪♪

30:47.210 --> 30:49.460
Can you ever forgive me?

30:49.460 --> 30:51.710
[ Laughs ]

30:51.710 --> 30:53.080
Of course.

30:53.080 --> 30:55.250
[ Exhales]

30:55.250 --> 30:57.210
[ Chuckles ]

30:57.210 --> 30:59.420
[ Voice breaking ]
That's good.

30:59.420 --> 31:01.920
Because now we have
a new mission.

31:01.920 --> 31:04.790
And I'm gonna need
your help.

31:06.750 --> 31:08.460
[ Buzzer ]

31:11.540 --> 31:12.580
[ Door closes ]

31:12.580 --> 31:14.420
Water?

31:17.170 --> 31:18.380
Let's try this
one more time.

31:18.380 --> 31:19.920
Are you sure there's no one
you want to call?

31:19.920 --> 31:21.120
Just let me out of here.

31:21.120 --> 31:22.670
I can't do that.

31:22.670 --> 31:25.290
Not till I know you have
a place to go. Or a valid ID.

31:25.290 --> 31:27.040
You got to
help me out here.

31:29.040 --> 31:30.710
Okay.

31:30.710 --> 31:32.960
You enjoy your water.

31:32.960 --> 31:34.620
We'll try this again
in a bit.

31:35.830 --> 31:37.620
[ Door opens ]

31:37.620 --> 31:40.000
Do you think you could
turn that around for me

31:40.000 --> 31:42.750
in the next couple hours?

31:42.750 --> 31:44.210
All right.

31:44.210 --> 31:46.120
All right.
Thanks, Martin.

31:46.120 --> 31:47.880
Yeah, I owe you one, man.

31:47.880 --> 31:51.920
Well, looks like we got
a guest for the night.

31:51.920 --> 31:53.290
I thought you
cut them all loose.

31:53.290 --> 31:55.540
I did.
But this one's got no ID.

31:55.540 --> 31:57.250
Won't talk.
I think she might be homeless.

31:57.250 --> 31:58.670
Ah.

31:58.670 --> 32:00.040
What's wrong?

32:01.380 --> 32:04.290
Lindauer?
He wanted me to see it.

32:04.290 --> 32:06.250
I see Emma's body.

32:06.250 --> 32:08.920
I witness the recovery
the "murder weapon".

32:08.920 --> 32:10.960
That doesn't give me
much to go off of

32:10.960 --> 32:12.670
if I keep investigating him.

32:12.670 --> 32:14.250
So you still think that
we got the wrong guy?

32:14.250 --> 32:15.580
That this Paul guy
is nothing?

32:15.580 --> 32:17.880
Oh, I know what a body looks
like 10 days in the ground.

32:17.880 --> 32:19.120
That wasn't it.

32:19.120 --> 32:20.620
But...

32:20.620 --> 32:23.080
look what I found
on Emma's body.

32:23.080 --> 32:24.250
Key fob.

32:24.250 --> 32:25.750
Yeah.

32:25.750 --> 32:27.290
Could have some
information on it.

32:27.290 --> 32:29.380
Yeah, like where
and when she drove.

32:29.380 --> 32:31.420
The new ones?
They record everything.

32:31.420 --> 32:33.460
This may tell us
what happened to her

32:33.460 --> 32:35.290
the night she disappeared.

32:35.290 --> 32:37.250
They found a body
buried up there.

32:37.250 --> 32:38.920
Been there like a week.

32:38.920 --> 32:41.710
Do they know who did it?

32:41.710 --> 32:43.580
One of the survivors,
I guess.

32:43.580 --> 32:45.880
I don't know, man,
maybe you're right.

32:45.880 --> 32:48.170
Maybe they deserve
to be locked up.

32:48.170 --> 32:49.750
[ Knock on door ]

32:49.750 --> 32:51.460
Okay, man, I got to go.

32:58.380 --> 32:59.540
You lost?

33:03.120 --> 33:05.080
You believe in destiny?

33:05.080 --> 33:07.170
No.

33:07.170 --> 33:13.170
♪♪

33:13.880 --> 33:16.290
You might want to start.

33:16.290 --> 33:19.540
♪♪

33:19.540 --> 33:23.000
♪♪

33:23.000 --> 33:26.500
♪♪

33:26.500 --> 33:29.790
♪♪

33:39.960 --> 33:42.080
[ Machine screeching, clicking ]

33:45.710 --> 33:48.000
High-frequency
sonic discharge.

33:48.000 --> 33:49.330
It'll keep her alert.

33:49.330 --> 33:52.540
We can't have her
shutting down again.

33:52.540 --> 33:54.290
So you don't need me
anymore.

33:54.290 --> 33:56.250
I was under
the impression

33:56.250 --> 33:58.960
that I'd be able to come back
and study her.

33:58.960 --> 34:00.460
Of course.

34:00.460 --> 34:02.790
That was our agreement,
and I'll honor it.

34:02.790 --> 34:05.380
I'm going to need to
search your bag, though.

34:06.750 --> 34:09.040
You're welcome to conduct
your research here,

34:09.040 --> 34:11.120
but I can't have you
taking it out of the lab.

34:11.120 --> 34:16.380
♪♪

34:16.380 --> 34:22.290
♪♪

34:22.290 --> 34:23.920
Thank you.

34:23.920 --> 34:25.920
I'll see you tomorrow.

34:25.920 --> 34:30.330
♪♪

34:30.330 --> 34:34.540
♪♪

34:34.540 --> 34:39.210
♪♪

34:39.210 --> 34:42.330
[ Screeching, clicking
continue ]

34:49.420 --> 34:53.250
♪♪

34:53.250 --> 34:55.710
[ Breathing heavily ]

34:55.710 --> 35:00.620
♪♪

35:00.620 --> 35:05.670
♪♪

35:05.670 --> 35:10.420
♪♪

35:14.210 --> 35:16.500
Why do I need to say
all this?

35:16.500 --> 35:19.250
Why not just
tell them the truth?

35:19.250 --> 35:21.250
Because the truth
is dangerous.

35:24.750 --> 35:26.540
[ Exhales ]

35:26.540 --> 35:30.330
Last year
I traveled to Africa.

35:30.330 --> 35:33.790
I went on safari
in Tanzania.

35:33.790 --> 35:36.170
Paul, you should've
seen it.

35:36.170 --> 35:39.540
There were elephants,
actual elephants.

35:39.540 --> 35:45.540
But, um, I also saw some things
that alarmed me.

35:45.790 --> 35:50.460
There are people there
who don't believe in science.

35:50.460 --> 35:53.290
They believe in superstition.
Witchcraft.

35:54.830 --> 35:58.880
For instance, they believe
that albino people are magical,

35:58.880 --> 36:00.620
so they hunt them.

36:00.620 --> 36:03.290
They dismember them.
Strip their bodies for parts.

36:03.290 --> 36:05.040
Sell their bones
on the street.

36:05.040 --> 36:08.420
The albinos have become
like a commodity.

36:08.420 --> 36:09.750
Hm.

36:09.750 --> 36:12.000
If you...

36:12.000 --> 36:14.920
If you tell the truth
about where we're from,

36:14.920 --> 36:17.040
we will become
a commodity.

36:19.040 --> 36:21.580
Now, there -- there are many
wonderful things

36:21.580 --> 36:24.210
about this time,
but it isn't without dangers.

36:24.210 --> 36:27.500
And we have to be
very careful.

36:27.500 --> 36:29.830
No one can know the truth.

36:29.830 --> 36:34.920
♪♪

36:34.920 --> 36:39.960
♪♪

36:39.960 --> 36:45.040
♪♪

36:45.040 --> 36:50.040
♪♪

36:50.040 --> 36:55.120
♪♪

