♪♪

37:20.580 --> 37:22.170
[ Knock on door ]

37:26.460 --> 37:28.670
Welcome, Rebecca.

37:28.670 --> 37:33.960
♪♪

37:33.960 --> 37:39.210
♪♪

37:39.210 --> 37:42.250
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

37:44.170 --> 37:45.920
-Martin.
-Martin: Hey, Jude,

37:45.920 --> 37:48.460
so I ran the serial
for the key fob you sent me.

37:48.460 --> 37:50.790
I got the geodata.
Just e-mailed it to you.

37:50.790 --> 37:52.790
Great.
Thanks for the rush, man.

37:52.790 --> 37:54.250
You got it.

37:54.250 --> 37:55.960
This have to do
with your missing agent?

37:57.380 --> 37:59.580
She's not missing
anymore, Martin.

37:59.580 --> 38:00.920
Thanks.

38:00.920 --> 38:02.540
No problem.

38:09.000 --> 38:12.330
♪♪

38:12.330 --> 38:15.250
Where did you go, Emma?

38:15.250 --> 38:18.830
♪♪

38:18.830 --> 38:23.080
♪♪

38:23.080 --> 38:25.080
I can't believe
we're here.

38:25.080 --> 38:27.330
And this is only
the beginning.

38:31.290 --> 38:33.580
When will I meet
the others?

38:33.580 --> 38:35.580
Soon.

38:35.580 --> 38:37.460
I just, um...

38:37.460 --> 38:40.290
I just want this time
for us.

38:40.290 --> 38:42.250
Just us.

38:50.000 --> 38:53.120
God, you know, there's --
there's so much to see here,

38:53.120 --> 38:57.120
and yet they always seem
to be looking at their phones.

38:57.120 --> 38:58.960
[ Laughs ]

38:58.960 --> 39:00.790
[ Sighs ]

39:00.790 --> 39:04.750
The Long Peace, it's a...

39:04.750 --> 39:07.170
it's a strange time.

39:09.080 --> 39:11.170
If they only knew
that the future held.

39:13.080 --> 39:16.120
The future is
in our hands, Paul.

39:16.120 --> 39:20.790
♪♪

39:20.790 --> 39:26.500
♪♪

39:26.500 --> 39:30.040
Paul: We believe that
this life is a test.

39:30.040 --> 39:31.790
And, as frightening
as it may be,

39:31.790 --> 39:35.500
we are living in a time
where we must face our fears.

39:35.500 --> 39:39.380
That's all we were doing
that night in the water.

39:39.380 --> 39:41.210
♪♪

39:41.210 --> 39:43.540
No boat, no life jackets...

39:43.540 --> 39:46.750
We wanted to drown.

39:46.750 --> 39:49.710
You can't be ready
for Judgment Day

39:49.710 --> 39:51.500
if you're afraid of death.

39:51.500 --> 39:53.290
[ Chuckles ]

39:53.290 --> 39:58.000
450 heroes crossed
that finish line.

39:58.000 --> 40:02.330
And those of us
who survived...

40:04.580 --> 40:07.500
...we're still trying to find
a way to join them.

40:07.500 --> 40:09.750
And we will.

40:09.750 --> 40:12.670
♪♪

40:12.670 --> 40:14.540
We will.

40:14.540 --> 40:16.290
♪♪

40:16.290 --> 40:18.420
[ Keyboard clicks ]

40:18.420 --> 40:22.040
[ Exhales sharply ]

40:22.040 --> 40:23.710
Is there any other way?

40:23.710 --> 40:25.420
♪♪

40:25.420 --> 40:28.380
I wish there was.

40:28.380 --> 40:32.500
When the survivors in the camp
take their own lives

40:32.500 --> 40:35.750
in what appears to be
a ritual suicide,

40:35.750 --> 40:38.080
this will explain why.

